video_analysis.transcript: but my mom booked a hair appointment for me last month and I completely forgot about it until last night. So I decided to just watch all my recorded lectures tonight. As usual, I got up, I got ready, I did my makeup. I say good morning to Kiki. She's always waiting for me. And my mom was so sweet enough to drop me off at the salon. Part of growing up is realizing that you don't need your mom to explain your haircut to the hairdresser anymore. And I used to be so shy and so quiet as a kid. It's like you suddenly notice you're not a kid anymore. Anyways, it's a small thing but it still feels a bit weird. After that I took myself out for lunch. There's this new cafe downtown so I figured it was the perfect excuse for a little solo date. I unfortunately did wait in line for 20 minutes. But when the banana bread matcha food came out, it was absolutely worth it. I highly recommend checking it out. It's literally my new favorite cafe. Then I made my commute home. When I got home, I immediately started working on a really exciting collab with one of my favorite clothing brands. I'm sure you guys already can guess who. It feels absolutely surreal to be working with them. And then I spent the rest of the day catching up on schoolwork and assignments and that pretty much wrapped up my day.
